<subSubSection id="B6DC9EABFFEAFFB0FF36761EDAB0FC62" pageId="91" pageNumber="104" type="description">
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFEAFFB0FF36761ED943FCCC" blockId="91.[189,514,787,847]" box="[189,315,825,847]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">
(
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FF4A761ED94DFCCC" box="[193,309,825,847]" captionStart="Figs 160–180" captionStartId="17.[151,191,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1397,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-153@17.[151,1398,232,1964]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 160–180. Tetrabothrus borneensis, holotype (160–162), T. punctiventris (163–166), T. sulawesicus (167–169), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (170–172), Z. gibbus, holotype (173–177), and Z. quasar, holotype (178–180): forebody (160, 163, 167, 170, 173, 178); antenna (161, 164, 168, 171, 174, 179); abdomen (162, 165, 169, 172, 175, 180); tergite VIII (166); tergite III (176); tergites VII– VIII (177). Scale bars: 160–165, 167–175, 178–180: 1.0 mm; 166, 176–177: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421194/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">Figs 173–177</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFEAFFB0FF1C764EDAB0FC62" blockId="91.[151,756,873,993]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">
This species was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FFEAFFB0FE61764EDAFFFC02" author="ASSING, V." box="[490,647,873,897]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104" pagination="87 - 175" refId="ref76876" refString="ASSING, V. 2016: A revision of Zyras STEPHENS sensu strictu of China, Taiwan, and Hong Kong, with records and (re-) descriptions of some species from other regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Lomechusini). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 9: 87 - 175." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. However, since the 
<typeStatus id="217D7382FFEAFFB0FF7176AED920FC22" box="[250,344,905,929]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">holotype</typeStatus>
was received only after the submission of the manuscript, it was not figured. The external characters of the 
<typeStatus id="217D7382FFEAFFB0FE9576EED904FC62" box="[286,380,969,993]" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">holotype</typeStatus>
are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="66FDD1A5FFEAFFB0FDBE76EEDABDFC62" box="[565,709,969,993]" captionStart="Figs 160–180" captionStartId="17.[151,191,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1397,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-153@17.[151,1398,232,1964]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 160–180. Tetrabothrus borneensis, holotype (160–162), T. punctiventris (163–166), T. sulawesicus (167–169), Zyras illecebrosus, paratype (170–172), Z. gibbus, holotype (173–177), and Z. quasar, holotype (178–180): forebody (160, 163, 167, 170, 173, 178); antenna (161, 164, 168, 171, 174, 179); abdomen (162, 165, 169, 172, 175, 180); tergite VIII (166); tergite III (176); tergites VII– VIII (177). Scale bars: 160–165, 167–175, 178–180: 1.0 mm; 166, 176–177: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6421194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6421194/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="104">Figs 173–177</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
